   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="edition"><!-- transcription goes here -->
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Bonus">Bono</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Innocens">Innocenti</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Benedictus">B
                    <lb n="2" break="no"/>enedicto</name>
               </persName>, qui bixit <choice>
                  <sic>na</sic>
                  <corr>
                     <expan><abbr>an</abbr><ex>os</ex></expan>
                  </corr>
               </choice>
               <num value="4">IIII</num>,
                    <lb n="3"/>et dies <num value="20">XX</num>.
                </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p/>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary"><!-- notes go here -->
            <p>Lines are uneven, no spaces or interpuncts indicate word endings. The
                    letter “T” is especially troublesome, as the horizontal stroke is shallow and
                    often off center. Line 1: as an example of the incosistent size of the letters,
                    the first o in Bono is little more than 1 cm high, the second is more than 2 cm
                    high. Line 2: “b” for “v” in vixit indicates a shift to vulgar pronunciation, and indicates a late date. The end of line 2
                    is very difficult to read, due either to incidental scratching or a mistake of
                    the carver, which he then tried to fix. Where I have corrected the text to read
                    “an(nos)” the stone reads “NA” with a line above it.</p>
         </div>
